This paper discusses bibliometric analysis of funding acknowledgment, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves collecting and analyzing data from citation index databases. It also touches on cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it mentions potential biases in the analysis. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the distribution of funding acknowledgment by language and type. Finally, it could be relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it mentions the importance of using caution when conducting bibliometric analysis.
